All Progressives Congress (APC) presidential candidate, Asíwájú Bola Tinubu, has commiserated with Works and Housing Minister Babatunde Raji Fashola on the death of his uncle, Chief Salmon Kayode Fashola, popularly called Uncle Kay. The late Fashola, the Giwa Olori Giwa Adinni, died yesterday and his remains were buried same day in accordance with Islamic rites. In a statement yesterday by Mr. Tunde Rahman of his media office, the APC presidential candidate urged the minister, family members and others left behind by the deceased to take heart and accept his passing as the will of Almighty Allah. While praying to God to grant the bereaved family the strength to bear the loss, he also beseeched Munificent Allah to admit the deceased to Al-Jannah Fir’daus.